        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 4:32PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 431 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Maylene, or 8 miles northwest of Montevallo,
moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hebron and Marvel.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
